{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014tSWMdgwEJsvozEx265VAX","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t\"\"\"Object types that are common across different environments.\"\"\"\n2\t\n3\tfrom relational_structs import Type\n4\t\n5\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures: dict[Type, list[str]] = {}\n6\t\n7\t# All geoms have an origin (x, y) and a rotation (in radians), and a bit\n8\t# indicating whether the geom is static (versus movable). They also have RGB.\n9\t# The z_order is an integer used for collision checking.\n10\tGeom2DType = Type(\"geom2d\")\n11\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[Geom2DType] = [\n12\t    \"x\",\n13\t    \"y\",\n14\t    \"theta\",\n15\t    \"static\",\n16\t    \"color_r\",\n17\t    \"color_g\",\n18\t    \"color_b\",\n19\t    \"z_order\",\n20\t]\n21\t# Specific geom types.\n22\tRectangleType = Type(\"rectangle\", parent=Geom2DType)\n23\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[RectangleType] = Geom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[Geom2DType] + [\n24\t    \"width\",\n25\t    \"height\",\n26\t]\n27\tCircleType = Type(\"circle\", parent=Geom2DType)\n28\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[CircleType] = Geom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[Geom2DType] + [\n29\t    \"radius\"\n30\t]\n31\tLObjectType = Type(\"lobject\", parent=Geom2DType)\n32\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[LObjectType] = Geom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[Geom2DType] + [\n33\t    \"width\",\n34\t    \"length_side1\",\n35\t    \"length_side2\",\n36\t]\n37\t\n38\t# Double-order rectangle (for shelves with bookends, etc.)\n39\tDoubleRectType = Type(\"double_rectangle\", parent=Geom2DType)\n40\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[DoubleRectType] = Geom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[\n41\t    RectangleType\n42\t] + [\n43\t    \"x1\",\n44\t    \"y1\",\n45\t    \"theta1\",\n46\t    \"width1\",\n47\t    \"height1\",\n48\t    \"z_order1\",\n49\t    \"color_r1\",\n50\t    \"color_g1\",\n51\t    \"color_b1\",\n52\t]\n53\t# A robot with a circle base, a rectangle arm, and a vacuum rectangle gripper.\n54\t# The (x, y, theta) are for the center of the robot base circle. The base_radius\n55\t# is for that circle. The arm_joint is a distance between the center and the\n56\t# gripper. The arm_length is the max value of arm_joint. The vacuum_on is a bit\n57\t# for whether the vacuum is on.\n58\tCRVRobotType = Type(\"crv_robot\")\n59\tGeom2DRobotEnvTypeFeatures[CRVRobotType] = [\n60\t    \"x\",\n61\t    \"y\",\n62\t    \"theta\",\n63\t    \"base_radius\",\n64\t    \"arm_joint\",\n65\t    \"arm_length\",\n66\t    \"vacuum\",\n67\t    \"gripper_height\",\n68\t    \"gripper_width\",\n69\t]\n70\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01EvDNLFDLGEkB2aJrGXjQgy","session_id":"fd37b91c-ebd5-4910-858d-9dd025b7a813","uuid":"0f34df58-48ec-4159-8162-cced89911f4c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:58:58.272Z"}
