{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   Write a behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0` environment. The robot must place a target block onto a target surface, clearing up to 4 obstructions that may be blocking the surface. The approach must use separate behavior classes with preconditions and subgoals, with all observation parsing in `obs_helpers.py`, action generation in `act_helpers.py`, behaviors in `behaviors.py`, and a thin `approach.py` wrapper. No magic numbers allowed outside named constants.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Coordinate convention (CRITICAL)**: Rectangle objects' (x,y) in observation = BOTTOM-LEFT CORNER (not center). Robot (x,y) = CENTER of circular base. Confirmed by printing vertex data.\n   - **Gripper geometry (θ=-π/2, arm down)**: Gripper center at (robot_x, robot_y−arm_joint); spans x=[robot_x±0.035], y=[robot_y−arm_joint±0.005]. Gripper height=0.07 (perpendicular/horizontal), width=0.01 (along arm/vertical).\n   - **Suction zone**: At distance arm_joint+0.015 from robot center along arm direction. Suction spans same ±0.035 horizontal. Suction zone has ZOrder=NONE → no collision with anything.\n   - **Pickup height window**: No-collision requires robot_y > obj_top+0.105; suction reaches when robot_y ≤ obj_top+0.110. PICKUP_OFFSET = 0.108 (midpoint). Formula: `pickup_robot_y = obj_top + 0.108`\n   - **ZOrder collision rules**: NONE(101) doesn't collide; SURFACE(2) collides with SURFACE+ALL; ALL(100) collides with everything. Target_surface has z_order=101=NONE, so target_surface doesn't cause collisions. Robot gripper/arm have SURFACE z_order → collide with obstructions (ALL).\n   - **Suctioned objects**: Excluded from obstacle group → robot can pass through them; no robot-vs-held-object collision check.\n   - **No gravity**: Objects stay wherever released (no physics gravity simulation).\n   - **Block x tracking**: When robot_x changes by Δ while holding object, block_x changes by same Δ. Block center_x ≈ robot_x at deposit time.\n   - **Deposit strategy**: Must deposit at TABLE LEVEL (dep_y = pick_y), not floating in mid-air, to avoid mid-air blocking collisions.\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`obs_helpers.py`** (created, revised):\n     ```python\n     # BOTTOM-LEFT corner convention for rectangles\n     ROBOT_X=0, ROBOT_Y=1, ROBOT_THETA=2, ROBOT_BASE_R=3, ROBOT_ARM_JOINT=4\n     ROBOT_ARM_LEN=5, ROBOT_VACUUM=6, ROBOT_GRIP_H=7, ROBOT_GRIP_W=8\n     SURF_X=9, SURF_Y=10, SURF_W=17, SURF_H=18\n     BLOCK_X=19, BLOCK_Y=20, BLOCK_W=27, BLOCK_H=28\n     OBS_BASE=29, OBS_STRIDE=10, NUM_OBS=4\n     OBS_REL_X=0, OBS_REL_Y=1, OBS_REL_W=8, OBS_REL_H=9\n     IS_ON_TOL=0.025\n\n     def get_surface(obs):  # returns {x,y,w,h,cx,top}  cx=x+w/2, top=y+h\n     def get_block(obs):    # returns {x,y,w,h,cx,top}\n     def get_obstruction(obs, i):  # returns {x,y,w,h,cx,top}\n     def obstruction_on_surface(obs, i):  # x-range strict overlap\n     def any_obstruction_on_surface(obs): # any obstruction overlaps surface\n     def is_block_on_surface(obs):  # checks bottom vertices in surface with tol\n     ```\n     is_block_on_surface uses: eff_y = block_y - IS_ON_TOL; checks (block_x, eff_y) and (block_x+block_w, eff_y) inside surface rect.\n\n   - **`act_helpers.py`** (created, revised multiple times):\n     ```python\n     DX_MAX=0.050, DY_MAX=0.050, DTHETA_MAX=0.196, DARM_MAX=0.100\n     ARM_MIN=0.10, ARM_MAX=0.20\n     GRIP_H=0.07, GRIP_W=0.01\n     SUCTION_REACH=0.015  # GRIP_W + GRIP_W/2\n     PICKUP_OFFSET=0.108  # total from obj_top; window is (0.105, 0.110)\n     CARRY_HEIGHT=0.700\n     DEPOSIT_X_POSITIONS=[0.15, 0.40, 1.25, 1.50]  # well-spaced, clear of surface\n     TARGET_THETA=-pi/2\n     XY_TOL=0.004, ARM_TOL=0.005, THETA_TOL=0.02\n\n     def pickup_robot_y(obj_top):\n         return obj_top + PICKUP_OFFSET  # NOT obj_top + ARM_MIN + PICKUP_OFFSET\n     def deposit_x_for_index(idx): return DEPOSIT_X_POSITIONS[idx % 4]\n     def correct_theta(current_theta): # angle_diff toward TARGET_THETA\n     def make_action(dx, dy, dtheta, darm, vac): # clamped 5-element array\n     ```\n\n   - **`behaviors.py`** (created, current state has bug in ClearObstructionsBehavior):\n     ```python\n     # FSM phases: PLAN→APPROACH_X→APPROACH_Y→CORRECT_THETA→VACUUM_ON→LIFT→CARRY_X→LOWER→VACUUM_OFF→DONE\n     \n     class ClearObstructionsBehavior(_PickPlaceFSM, Behavior):\n         def _start_plan(self, obs):\n             # BUG: sets self._dep_y = CARRY_HEIGHT  (should be self._pick_y)\n             for i in range(NUM_OBS):\n                 if obstruction_on_surface(obs, i):\n                     ob = get_obstruction(obs, i)\n                     self._pick_x = ob[\"cx\"]\n                     self._pick_y = pickup_robot_y(ob[\"top\"])\n                     self._dep_x  = deposit_x_for_index(self._dep_counter)\n                     self._dep_y  = CARRY_HEIGHT  # ← WRONG: should be self._pick_y\n     \n     class PickAndPlaceBehavior(_PickPlaceFSM, Behavior):\n         def _setup(self, obs):\n             b = get_block(obs)\n             s = get_surface(obs)\n             self._pick_x = b[\"cx\"]\n             self._pick_y = pickup_robot_y(b[\"top\"])\n             self._dep_x  = s[\"cx\"]\n             self._dep_y  = pickup_robot_y(b[\"top\"])  # ← CORRECT\n     ```\n\n   - **`approach.py`** (correct):\n     ```python\n     class GeneratedApproach:\n         def reset(self, state, info):\n             place = PickAndPlaceBehavior()\n             clear = ClearObstructionsBehavior()\n             if place.initializable(state):\n                 self._behaviors = deque([place])\n             else:\n                 self._behaviors = deque([clear, place])\n             self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n             self._current.reset(state)\n         \n         def get_action(self, state):\n             if self._current.terminated(state) and self._behaviors:\n                 self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n                 self._current.reset(state)\n             return self._current.step(state)\n     ```\n\n   - **`test_approach.py`**: Runs 5 seeds (0,1,2,3,42) with MAX_STEPS=2000, prints SUCCESS/TIMEOUT.\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **Error 1 - ObjectCentricState iteration**: `feats.items()` failed; fixed by iterating `for obj in feats` and using `feats[obj]`.\n   - **Error 2 - Wrong coordinate assumption**: Assumed (x,y) for rectangles was center; discovered via vertex inspection that it's BOTTOM-LEFT corner. This caused completely wrong pickup height calculations (robot target y was off by ~0.1).\n   - **Error 3 - pickup_robot_y formula**: Used `obj_top + ARM_MIN + PICKUP_OFFSET = obj_top + 0.208` instead of `obj_top + PICKUP_OFFSET = obj_top + 0.108`. Robot was targeting y=0.430 when it should target y=0.330 for obs0. Suction zone was too high to reach object. Fixed by removing ARM_MIN from formula.\n   - **Error 4 - Deposit collision (mid-air)**: Deposited obstructions floating at y≈0.460-0.592 blocked subsequent carry operations. When carrying target block toward surface (dep_x=0.586), block collided with obs3 deposited at x=0.333 (y≈0.459). Fixed by: (a) using dep_y=pick_y to land obstructions at table level, (b) changing DEPOSIT_X_POSITIONS from [0.15, 0.25, 1.35, 1.45] to [0.15, 0.40, 1.25, 1.50] for better separation.\n   - **Error 5 - Deposit positions overlap**: Initial [0.15, 0.25] positions: obs0 w=0.114→[0.093, 0.207]; obs3 w=0.195→[0.152, 0.348]; overlap at [0.152, 0.207]. Fixed to [0.15, 0.40] giving gap of 0.05 between them (max width 0.20 × 2 positions need 0.25 gap; 0.40-0.15=0.25 is marginal... but [0.093,0.207] vs [0.30,0.50] have no overlap).\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Discovered gripper-obstruction collision via `state_2d_has_collision` direct testing\n   - Found collision boundary: robot_y=0.325 causes collision, robot_y=0.330 doesn't for obs0 (top=0.222)\n   - Derived exact pickup window of 0.005 range: (obj_top+0.105, obj_top+0.110]\n   - Established block_x tracking: block_x_deposited = robot_dep_x - block_w/2; block_center = robot_dep_x\n   - Confirmed no gravity (objects stay where released)\n   - Confirmed target_surface z_order=NONE → no collision → can deposit through it\n   - Confirmed suctioned objects excluded from obstacles → no robot-vs-held collision\n   - Current ongoing issue: behaviors.py ClearObstructionsBehavior still uses dep_y=CARRY_HEIGHT\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - Initial environment specification (kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0, asking for behavior decomposition and approach.py)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Fix `ClearObstructionsBehavior._start_plan` in `behaviors.py`: change `self._dep_y = CARRY_HEIGHT` to `self._dep_y = self._pick_y`\n   - Run tests to verify all 5 seeds succeed\n   - If still failing, debug and fix remaining issues\n   - Git commit after each meaningful fix\n\n8. Current Work:\n   Just made edit to `act_helpers.py` changing DEPOSIT_X_POSITIONS from `[0.15, 0.25, 1.35, 1.45]` to `[0.15, 0.40, 1.25, 1.50]` to prevent deposit overlap. The test still showed timeout because `behaviors.py` still has `self._dep_y = CARRY_HEIGHT` in `ClearObstructionsBehavior._start_plan()`.\n\n   Debug trace from last run (seed 0, 250 steps):\n   - robot stuck at x=0.634, vac=1, phase=CARRY_X trying to reach dep_x=0.586\n   - block at x=0.568, y=0.459 (floating too high)\n   - obs3 deposited at x=0.333, y=0.459 (floating!) blocking path\n\n   Root cause confirmed: depositing at CARRY_HEIGHT means objects float at y≈0.459-0.592, blocking the target block's path when it's carried to the surface.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Fix `behaviors.py` `ClearObstructionsBehavior._start_plan` method: change `self._dep_y = CARRY_HEIGHT` to `self._dep_y = self._pick_y`. This makes obstructions land at table level (y≈0.100) rather than floating in mid-air, preventing the collision that blocks the robot at x=0.634.\n\n   From the most recent work:\n   ```python\n   # Current (WRONG) in ClearObstructionsBehavior._start_plan:\n   self._dep_y  = CARRY_HEIGHT      # release in mid-air (no gravity)\n   \n   # Should be:\n   self._dep_y  = self._pick_y      # release at table level\n   ```\n   This is the critical remaining fix before testing.\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/node/.claude/projects/-sandbox/fd37b91c-ebd5-4910-858d-9dd025b7a813.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd37b91c-ebd5-4910-858d-9dd025b7a813","uuid":"ef061034-6b60-484c-a958-45633e9c27f6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:29:47.946Z","isSynthetic":true}
