n logic, and test it. Though I should reconsider the exclusion zone—it shouldn't blindly use ARM_MIN if the obstacle itself is narrower than that distance.\n\nFor the deposited obstruction to avoid colliding with the robot base, I need to ensure their x-ranges don't overlap. The obstruction spans [dep_x - carried_w/2, dep_x + carried_w/2] and the robot base spans [block_cx - ARM_MIN, block_cx + ARM_MIN], so either the obstruction must be entirely to the right or entirely to the left. In the deposit function, I'm defining a clearance zone around the deposit point using half = max(carried_w/2, ARM_MIN) + 0.01 to enforce this separation. half = ARM_MIN + 0.01 (when ARM_MIN > carried_w/2), then:\n- [dep_x-0.110, dep_x+0.110] doesn't overlap [block_cx-0.100, block_cx+0.100]\n- This means dep_x > block_cx + 0.210 OR dep_x < block_cx - 0.210\n- The deposited obs at [dep_x-w/2, dep_x+w/2] doesn't overlap [block_cx-0.100, block_cx+0.100] ✓\n\nThis seems correct. The block check [block_cx-ARM_MIN, block_cx+ARM_MIN] = [block_cx-0.100, block_cx+0.100] combined with clearance half=0.110 means deposited obs must be at least 0.210 away from block_cx.\n\nFor seed 1 with block_cx=1.399, I'm testing placement positions for obs1 (w=0.178, half=0.110). At x=0.60, I'm checking overlaps against the block exclusion zone, obs0, the surface, and obs2, finding no conflicts so far.\n\nI think the issue is the surface expansion I added—it's making the exclusion zone too large. Let me revert those changes to just use the surface bounds directly without the ARM_MIN padding, while keeping the block exclusion logic intact.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":309,"cache_read_input_tokens":96334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":309},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null