{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   Write a behavior-based approach for `kinder/Obstruction2D-o4-v0` — a robot that clears up to 4 obstructions from a target surface and then places a target block on that surface. The approach uses separate behavior classes (`ClearObstructionsBehavior`, `PickAndPlaceBehavior`) with preconditions and deterministic FSM-based policies. All observation parsing lives in `obs_helpers.py`, action helpers in `act_helpers.py`, behaviors in `behaviors.py`, with a thin `approach.py` wrapper. The code must be robust across many random seeds.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - **Coordinate convention**: Rectangle objects (x,y) = BOTTOM-LEFT CORNER. Robot (x,y) = CENTER of circular base.\n   - **Robot base radius**: ARM_MIN = 0.100 (minimum arm extension = base radius). The robot base CIRCLE can collide with objects.\n   - **Pickup height window**: pick_y = obj_top + 0.108 (window [obj_top+0.105, obj_top+0.110]; formula: `pickup_robot_y(obj_top) = obj_top + PICKUP_OFFSET = obj_top + 0.108`).\n   - **No gravity**: Objects stay wherever released (no physics gravity).\n   - **Suctioned objects**: Excluded from obstacle group for robot collision, but may still collide with other environment objects.\n   - **FSM phases**: RAISE → APPROACH_X → APPROACH_Y → CORRECT_THETA → VACUUM_ON → LIFT → CARRY_X → LOWER → VACUUM_OFF → DONE\n   - **CARRY_HEIGHT = 0.700**: safe height for lateral movement.\n   - **dep_y = pick_y**: deposit at table level (not mid-air).\n   - **Target surface z_order=NONE**: doesn't cause collisions with anything.\n   - **sort-by-top**: Process obstructions tallest-first to avoid robot base circle colliding with adjacent taller obstructions during approach to shorter ones.\n   - **Dynamic deposit x**: `choose_deposit_x` scans x positions avoiding surface, other obstructions, block approach zone, and robot-base-vs-block during LOWER.\n   - **safe_pick_x**: When the robot base at ob_cx would collide with a nearby non-picked obstruction during APPROACH_Y, scan across ob's x-range to find a collision-free approach x.\n   - **Obstruction offset after deposit**: When `safe_pick_x` returns pick_x ≠ ob_cx, the deposited object ends up at `dep_x + (ob_cx - pick_x)`, not `dep_x`. This must be accounted for in surface overlap checks.\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`obs_helpers.py`** (existing, unchanged in current session):\n     - ROBOT_X=0..ROBOT_GRIP_W=8, SURF_X=9/SURF_Y=10/SURF_W=17/SURF_H=18\n     - BLOCK_X=19/BLOCK_Y=20/BLOCK_W=27/BLOCK_H=28\n     - OBS_BASE=29, OBS_STRIDE=10, NUM_OBS=4\n     - `get_robot/get_surface/get_block/get_obstruction` all return dicts including `cx`, `top`\n     - `get_obstruction` returns: `{x, y, w, h, cx, top}` where `top = y + h`\n     - `obstruction_on_surface(obs, i)`: strict x-range overlap with surface\n     - `any_obstruction_on_surface(obs)`: any of 4 obstructions overlaps surface\n     - `is_block_on_surface(obs)`: checks bottom vertices of block inside surface with IS_ON_TOL=0.025\n     - `intervals_overlap_strict(lo1, hi1, lo2, hi2)`: True if open intervals overlap\n\n   - **`act_helpers.py`** (heavily modified — current version):\n     ```python\n     ARM_MIN = 0.10  # base radius\n     GRIP_HALF_H = 0.035  # suction horizontal half-width\n     PICKUP_OFFSET = 0.108\n     CARRY_HEIGHT = 0.700\n     DEPOSIT_X_SCAN_START = 0.15\n     DEPOSIT_X_SCAN_END = 1.55\n     DEPOSIT_X_SCAN_STEP = 0.05\n     PICK_X_SCAN_STEP = 0.005\n     \n     def pickup_robot_y(obj_top): return obj_top + PICKUP_OFFSET\n     \n     def _circle_rect_dist(cx, cy, rx, ry, rw, rh):\n         px = np.clip(cx, rx, rx+rw)\n         py = np.clip(cy, ry, ry+rh)\n         return np.sqrt((cx-px)**2 + (cy-py)**2)\n     \n     def safe_pick_x(obs, ob_idx, ob, pick_y):\n         \"\"\"Scan ob's x-range [ob.x+GRIP_HALF_H, ob.x+ob.w-GRIP_HALF_H] to find\n         collision-free robot x for approach (checks all other obstructions).\"\"\"\n         half_h = GRIP_HALF_H\n         lo = ob[\"x\"] + half_h; hi = ob[\"x\"] + ob[\"w\"] - half_h\n         if lo > hi: lo = hi = ob[\"cx\"]\n         for x in np.arange(lo, hi+1e-9, PICK_X_SCAN_STEP):\n             ok = True\n             for j in range(NUM_OBS):\n                 if j == ob_idx: continue\n                 ob_j = get_obstruction(obs, j)\n                 d = _circle_rect_dist(x, pick_y, ob_j[\"x\"], ob_j[\"y\"],\n                                       ob_j[\"w\"], ob_j[\"top\"]-ob_j[\"y\"])\n                 if d < ARM_MIN + 0.005: ok = False; break\n             if ok: return x\n         return ob[\"cx\"]\n     \n     def choose_deposit_x(obs, carried_idx, carried_ob, block_ob):\n         \"\"\"Scan x, return first position clear of: surface, block approach zone,\n         block during LOWER (robot base), and all other obstructions.\"\"\"\n         carried_w = carried_ob[\"w\"]; carried_top = carried_ob[\"top\"]\n         dep_y = pickup_robot_y(carried_top)\n         block_lo = block_ob[\"x\"]; block_hi = block_ob[\"x\"]+block_ob[\"w\"]\n         block_top = block_ob[\"top\"]; block_cx = block_ob[\"cx\"]\n         half = max(carried_w/2, ARM_MIN) + 0.01\n         \n         x = DEPOSIT_X_SCAN_START\n         while x <= DEPOSIT_X_SCAN_END + 1e-9:\n             lo, hi = x-half, x+half\n             # 1. Avoid surface\n             if intervals_overlap_strict(lo, hi, s[\"x\"], s[\"x\"]+s[\"w\"]):\n                 x += step; continue\n             # 2. Avoid block approach zone (object extent vs robot-at-block)\n             dep_lo_obj = x - carried_w/2; dep_hi_obj = x + carried_w/2\n             if intervals_overlap_strict(dep_lo_obj, dep_hi_obj, block_cx-ARM_MIN, block_cx+ARM_MIN):\n                 x += step; continue\n             # 3. Robot base at (x, dep_y) vs block during LOWER\n             if dep_y < block_top + ARM_MIN:\n                 if intervals_overlap_strict(x-ARM_MIN, x+ARM_MIN, block_lo, block_hi):\n                     x += step; continue\n             # 4. Avoid all other obstructions (robot base clearance)\n             for j in range(NUM_OBS):\n                 if j == carried_idx: continue\n                 ob = get_obstruction(obs, j)\n                 if intervals_overlap_strict(lo, hi, ob[\"x\"], ob[\"x\"]+ob[\"w\"]):\n                     blocked = True; break\n             if not blocked: return x\n             x += step\n         return DEPOSIT_X_SCAN_START\n     ```\n\n   - **`behaviors.py`** (heavily modified — current version):\n     ```python\n     # FSM phases\n     _P_RAISE = \"RAISE\"  # NEW: lift to CARRY_HEIGHT before lateral movement\n     _P_APPROACH_X, _P_APPROACH_Y, _P_CORRECT_TH, _P_VACUUM_ON\n     _P_LIFT, _P_CARRY_X, _P_LOWER, _P_VACUUM_OFF, _P_DONE\n     \n     class _PickPlaceFSM:\n         # RAISE phase: lift to CARRY_HEIGHT, retract arm\n         # APPROACH_X: move x to pick_x at CARRY_HEIGHT\n         # APPROACH_Y: lower to pick_y\n         # CORRECT_THETA → VACUUM_ON → LIFT → CARRY_X → LOWER → VACUUM_OFF → DONE\n     \n     class ClearObstructionsBehavior(_PickPlaceFSM, Behavior):\n         def terminated(self, obs):\n             return self._fsm_done() and not any_obstruction_on_surface(obs)\n         \n         def _start_plan(self, obs):\n             # Sort by top height descending (tallest first)\n             candidates = [(i, get_obstruction(obs,i)) for i in range(NUM_OBS)\n                           if obstruction_on_surface(obs,i)]\n             if not candidates: self._phase = _P_DONE; return\n             i, ob = max(candidates, key=lambda t: t[1][\"top\"])\n             block = get_block(obs)\n             pick_y = pickup_robot_y(ob[\"top\"])\n             self._pick_y = pick_y\n             self._pick_x = safe_pick_x(obs, i, ob, pick_y)\n             self._dep_x  = choose_deposit_x(obs, i, ob, block)\n             self._dep_y  = self._pick_y   # table level\n             self._phase  = _P_RAISE\n     \n     class PickAndPlaceBehavior(_PickPlaceFSM, Behavior):\n         def terminated(self, obs): return is_block_on_surface(obs)\n         def _setup(self, obs):\n             b = get_block(obs); s = get_surface(obs)\n             self._pick_x = b[\"cx\"]; self._pick_y = pickup_robot_y(b[\"top\"])\n             self._dep_x  = s[\"cx\"]; self._dep_y  = pickup_robot_y(b[\"top\"])\n             self._phase  = _P_RAISE\n     ```\n\n   - **`approach.py`** (unchanged from previous session):\n     ```python\n     class GeneratedApproach:\n         def reset(self, state, info):\n             place = PickAndPlaceBehavior()\n             clear = ClearObstructionsBehavior()\n             if place.initializable(state):\n                 self._behaviors = deque([place])\n             else:\n                 self._behaviors = deque([clear, place])\n             self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n             self._current.reset(state)\n         \n         def get_action(self, state):\n             if self._current.terminated(state) and self._behaviors:\n                 self._current = self._behaviors.popleft()\n                 self._current.reset(state)\n             return self._current.step(state)\n     ```\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - **ImportError: `DEPOSIT_CLEAR_Y`**: Removed stale import from `behaviors.py`.\n   - **`dep_y = CARRY_HEIGHT` (mid-air deposit)**: Changed to `dep_y = self._pick_y` so objects land at table level.\n   - **APPROACH_X collision at y=0.330**: Robot at old pick_y tried to move x, but gripper collided with taller obstruction (top=0.233). Fixed by adding `_P_RAISE` phase to lift to CARRY_HEIGHT=0.700 first before lateral movement.\n   - **Premature behavior switch during CARRY_X**: When carried obstruction moved off the surface x-range during carry, `terminated()` fired early. Fixed by changing to `return self._fsm_done() and not any_obstruction_on_surface(obs)`.\n   - **APPROACH_Y stuck — adjacent obstruction blocks robot base circle**: For seeds 1, 42: tall obstruction near the target obstruction blocked robot from descending. Fixed by sorting obstructions tallest-first so tall ones are cleared before shorter ones.\n   - **LOWER stuck — carried object x-overlaps another obstruction**: For seeds 2, 3: dynamic dep_x chosen too close to an existing obstruction. Fixed by `choose_deposit_x` scanning for clear position.\n   - **Block exclusion too conservative**: When first added block exclusion check, used `half` (0.110) instead of `carried_w/2` (0.033 for small obs), making seed 2 fail again because dep_x=1.30 was rejected. Fixed by using `dep_lo_obj = x - carried_w/2`.\n   - **LOWER stuck — robot base vs block (seeds 8, 19)**: Robot base at dep_x during LOWER collided with the target block (dep_y < block_top + ARM_MIN and x-overlap). Fixed by adding check 3 in `choose_deposit_x`.\n   - **APPROACH_Y stuck — non-surface obstruction blocks approach (seed 314)**: obs1 (not on surface) at x=[1.370, 1.459] right next to obs3 on surface at x=[1.217, 1.370]. Robot at ob_cx=1.294 couldn't descend. Fixed by `safe_pick_x` scanning the object's x-range to find collision-free approach x.\n   - **Seed 1 regression (current bug)**: After introducing `safe_pick_x`, seed 1 loops infinitely. `safe_pick_x` returns pick_x=0.608 (shifted from obs1_cx=0.662 to avoid obs2 at cx=0.942). `choose_deposit_x` returns dep_x=0.600. After deposit, obs1 effective center = dep_x + (ob_cx - pick_x) = 0.600 + 0.054 = 0.654. obs1 right edge = 0.654+0.089=0.743 > surface_lo=0.720 → obs1 STILL overlaps surface! The same obstruction keeps being re-picked forever.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - All major single-seed bugs were identified and fixed through debug scripts that print robot position, phase, and obstruction positions every N steps.\n   - Broad test (28 seeds) revealed three remaining failures (8, 19, 314) after 5-seed suite passed.\n   - Seeds 8, 19: LOWER collision with block — needed `dep_y < block_top + ARM_MIN` y-overlap check in `choose_deposit_x`.\n   - Seed 314: APPROACH_Y blocked by non-surface obstruction — needed `safe_pick_x`.\n   - Current regression on seed 1: object not fully moved off surface because pick_x ≠ ob_cx introduces an x-offset that `choose_deposit_x` doesn't account for.\n\n6. All User Messages:\n   - Initial continuation message (no explicit text): The context summary and system files were provided for a session continuation; the user implicitly requested to resume fixing the approach.\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Fix seed 1 regression: `choose_deposit_x` must account for the offset `(ob_cx - pick_x)` when computing where the obstruction actually lands after deposit. The object's effective center after deposit = `dep_x + (ob_cx - pick_x)`. The surface overlap check (and possibly other checks) must use this effective center.\n   - After fixing, re-run the 28-seed broad test to verify seeds 8, 19, 314 (those recent LOWER/APPROACH fixes) also still work.\n   - Commit after each fix.\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The last action taken was running `debug5.py` for seed 1, which revealed an infinite loop where `ClearObstructionsBehavior` keeps picking obs1 (surface=True at cx≈0.65), depositing it at dep_x=0.600, and then finding it still on the surface. The root cause: `safe_pick_x` returns pick_x=0.608 (shifted left to avoid obs2's proximity), but obs1 has cx=0.662. After carry+deposit at dep_x=0.600, obs1's true center = 0.600 + (0.662 - 0.608) = 0.654. obs1 right edge = 0.743 still overlaps surface left edge 0.720.\n\n   The current `act_helpers.py` and `behaviors.py` are committed at git hash `93154f1`.\n\n   The current test results before the regression:\n   - Seed 0: SUCCESS\n   - Seed 1: TIMEOUT (regression from previous working state)\n   - Seed 2: SUCCESS\n   - Seed 3: SUCCESS\n   - Seed 42: SUCCESS\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Fix the seed 1 regression by updating `choose_deposit_x` to account for the pick_x → ob_cx offset. Pass `pick_x` and `ob_cx` (or the full `ob` dict plus `pick_x`) to `choose_deposit_x`, then compute:\n   ```python\n   eff_cx = x + (carried_ob[\"cx\"] - pick_x)\n   ```\n   Use `[eff_cx - carried_w/2, eff_cx + carried_w/2]` for:\n   - Surface overlap check (instead of `[lo, hi]`)\n   - Block approach zone check (instead of `[dep_lo_obj, dep_hi_obj]`)\n   - Other obstruction overlap check (instead of `[lo, hi]`)\n   \n   But keep `x ± ARM_MIN` for robot-base checks (LOWER collision). Also update the call in `behaviors._start_plan` to pass `self._pick_x` as an additional argument to `choose_deposit_x`.\n\n   Immediately before this summary request, the code was looping on seed 1 with:\n   > `pick_x=0.608 dep_x=0.600` — robot picks obs1 (cx≈0.662), carries to dep_x=0.600, but effective obs1 center after deposit = 0.654, still overlapping surface [0.720, 0.935] at right edge 0.743.\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/node/.claude/projects/-sandbox/fd37b91c-ebd5-4910-858d-9dd025b7a813.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd37b91c-ebd5-4910-858d-9dd025b7a813","uuid":"78f9b538-c760-41c7-b57e-ef0740d04902","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:58:04.253Z","isSynthetic":true}
